Notebook[{

Cell[CellGroupData[{
Cell["Homework 11", "Title",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8610359930508327`*^9, 
  3.861035996903749*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"afc9433b-c139-45b1-a69a-\
eff323ec04a2"],

Cell["\<\
Adam Prieto
Dr. Shelley Poole
MTH 3440 - Partial Differential Equations
9 May 2022\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8610688108480377`*^9, 
  3.861068839348328*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"dcbcb1d1-c1aa-4811-b63b-\
4ee6c3a83c06"],

Cell["Chapter 4 Problems", "Subtitle",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8611210777887297`*^9, 
  3.861121082499482*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"517ff86c-cdf6-4ac4-91dc-\
7762473a5f79"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["\<\
6.) Discuss the application of separation of variables in Polar and \
Cylindrical problems. How does it relate to the work you did in rectangular \
coordinates? What do you find most striking about the solution forms?\
\>", "Chapter",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.86112108644617*^9, 
  3.861121167279245*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"dc8d34a4-0aaf-4d9a-823a-\
eac53d2efa98"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Although the general process remains the same, separation of variables in \
Polar and Cylindrical coordinates is significantly harder than in \
rectangular. This is due to the fact that the definition of the derivatives \
in polar and cylindrical require many partial derivatives (and work) when \
deriving the desired formulas. Then comes substitution. This problem will \
become more apparent when discussing spherical coordinates, but for now just \
know that the algebra gets pretty messy and very complex. \n\nIn regards to \
the resulting ODEs, aside from the different variables, the equations \
themselves are identical to their rectangular counterparts, and can be solved \
as such. Problem 2 from chapter 4 produces the familiar ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{"R", "'"}], "+", 
     RowBox[{
      SuperscriptBox["\[Lambda]", "2"], "R"}]}], "=", "0"}], TraditionalForm]],
  FormatType->"TraditionalForm",ExpressionUUID->
  "bdd7d43f-8faf-4cfe-a353-8efbfe083f6b"],
 " equation that we\[CloseCurlyQuote]ve seen countless times already in this \
class, so we can get a solution fairly easily (check the previous work for \
the derivation). However, it\[CloseCurlyQuote]s important to note that not \
all the solutions are ",
 StyleBox["identical",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 " to the ones we seen before, since I had to manipulate the \[CapitalTheta](\
\[Theta]) equation; but, I was still able to get something reminiscent of \
what I\[CloseCurlyQuote]ve worked with before.  "
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.861121175220623*^9, 3.861121177713204*^9}, {
  3.861121218903808*^9, 3.861121488077783*^9}, {3.8611215485411987`*^9, 
  3.861121621830535*^9}, {3.86112165370271*^9, 
  3.8611219295753813`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"4d0a089a-819a-464d-9459-\
c508afb65db5"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell["Chapter 5 Problems", "Subtitle",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8610360030850286`*^9, 
  3.861036008537835*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"a3ed3cf1-1e4f-4728-9cd8-\
a843a81c87c5"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell[TextData[{
 "1.)Walk through the derivation of ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["u", "xx"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "e98fd895-c748-45e5-8437-d46fbf9635b8"],
 " in terms of (r, \[Theta], \[Phi]) and explain the steps. "
}], "Chapter",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8610360135856323`*^9, 3.8610360456356897`*^9}, {
  3.861037031076498*^9, 
  3.861037031909625*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"2cb1f6bd-fbe7-4105-824e-\
bfb5040eecba"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "When defining ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["u", "xx"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "9c9f9fd6-a899-4196-aa0c-4db42220e95d"],
 " in terms of (r, \[Theta], \[Phi]), we should first apply the chain rule as \
we did in polar coordinates. Doing so yields the following:\n",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    SubscriptBox["u", "xx"], "=", 
    RowBox[{
     SuperscriptBox[
      RowBox[{
       SubscriptBox["u", "\[Rho]\[Rho]"], "(", 
       SubscriptBox["\[Rho]", "x"], ")"}], "2"], "+", 
     RowBox[{
      SubscriptBox["u", "\[Rho]\[Theta]"], 
      SubscriptBox["\[Rho]", "x"], 
      SubscriptBox["\[Theta]", "x"]}], "+", 
     RowBox[{
      SubscriptBox["u", "\[Rho]\[Phi]"], 
      SubscriptBox["\[Rho]", "x"], 
      SubscriptBox["\[Phi]", "x"]}], "+", 
     RowBox[{
      SubscriptBox["u", "\[Rho]"], 
      SubscriptBox["\[Rho]", "xx"]}], "+", 
     SuperscriptBox[
      RowBox[{
       SubscriptBox["u", "\[Theta]\[Theta]"], "(", 
       SubscriptBox["\[Theta]", "x"], ")"}], "2"], "+", 
     RowBox[{
      SubscriptBox["u", "\[Theta]\[Rho]"], 
      SubscriptBox["\[Theta]", "x"], 
      SubscriptBox["\[Rho]", "x"]}], "+", 
     RowBox[{
      SubscriptBox["u", "\[Theta]\[Phi]"], 
      SubscriptBox["\[Theta]", "x"], 
      SubscriptBox["\[Phi]", "x"]}], "+", 
     RowBox[{
      SubscriptBox["u", "\[Theta]"], 
      SubscriptBox["\[Theta]", "xx"]}], "+", 
     SuperscriptBox[
      RowBox[{
       SubscriptBox["u", "\[Phi]\[Phi]"], "(", 
       SubscriptBox["\[Phi]", "x"], ")"}], "2"], "+", 
     RowBox[{
      SubscriptBox["u", "\[Phi]\[Rho]"], 
      SubscriptBox["\[Phi]", "x"], 
      SubscriptBox["\[Rho]", "x"]}], "+", 
     RowBox[{
      SubscriptBox["u", "\[Phi]\[Theta]"], 
      SubscriptBox["\[Phi]", "x"], 
      SubscriptBox["\[Theta]", "x"]}], "+", 
     RowBox[{
      SubscriptBox["u", "\[Phi]"], 
      RowBox[{
       SubscriptBox["\[Phi]", "xx"], "."}]}]}]}], TraditionalForm]],
  ExpressionUUID->"d4bc39ac-f16f-4dfc-9993-dc6a46c8cd47"],
 " (\[LeftArrow]This can also be found in the notes.)\nObviously, this \
equation is quite a bit to work with, and is made easier with Mathematica. \
That said, lets now define \[Rho], \[Theta], and \[Phi] in terms of the \
variables x, y, and z."
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8610360620852947`*^9, 3.8610366004249973`*^9}, {
  3.861122050224511*^9, 
  3.86112212454631*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"33a6418f-dc7e-48c7-b448-\
b4ba1815edc6"],

Cell[BoxData[{
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{"\[Rho]", "[", 
    RowBox[{"x_", ",", "y_", ",", "z_"}], "]"}], "=", 
   SqrtBox[
    RowBox[{
     SuperscriptBox["x", "2"], "+", 
     SuperscriptBox["y", "2"], "+", 
     SuperscriptBox["z", "2"]}]]}], ";"}], "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{"\[Theta]", "[", 
    RowBox[{"x_", ",", "y_", ",", "z_"}], "]"}], "=", 
   RowBox[{"ArcTan", "[", 
    RowBox[{
     SqrtBox[
      RowBox[{
       SuperscriptBox["x", "2"], "+", 
       SuperscriptBox["y", "2"]}]], "/", "z"}], "]"}]}], 
  ";"}], "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{"\[Phi]", "[", 
    RowBox[{"x_", ",", "y_", ",", "z_"}], "]"}], "=", 
   RowBox[{"ArcTan", "[", 
    RowBox[{"y", "/", "x"}], "]"}]}], ";"}]}], "Input",
 CellLabel->"In[1]:=",ExpressionUUID->"d6ddd2e4-8781-4ed4-9075-007ef6486148"],

Cell["\<\
The nice thing about Mathematica is that we can take infinitely many \
derivatives by only changing a few characters on a line. However, for our \
purposes, we only need the first and second derivatives of the above \
functions:\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.861036616064233*^9, 
  3.861036698716692*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"c1d5ab6b-d292-42ba-866b-\
3d2be6d51c64"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell[BoxData[{
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"a", "=", 
   RowBox[{"FullSimplify", "[", 
    RowBox[{"D", "[", 
     RowBox[{
      RowBox[{"\[Rho]", "[", 
       RowBox[{"x", ",", "y", ",", "z"}], "]"}], ",", 
      RowBox[{"{", 
       RowBox[{"x", ",", "1"}], "}"}]}], "]"}], "]"}]}], " ", 
  RowBox[{"(*", 
   SubscriptBox["\[Rho]", "x"], "*)"}]}], "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"b", "=", 
   RowBox[{"FullSimplify", "[", 
    RowBox[{"D", "[", 
     RowBox[{
      RowBox[{"\[Rho]", "[", 
       RowBox[{"x", ",", "y", ",", "z"}], "]"}], ",", 
      RowBox[{"{", 
       RowBox[{"x", ",", "2"}], "}"}]}], "]"}], "]"}]}], 
  RowBox[{"(*", 
   SubscriptBox["\[Rho]", "xx"], "*)"}]}], "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"c", "=", 
   RowBox[{"FullSimplify", "[", 
    RowBox[{"D", "[", 
     RowBox[{
      RowBox[{"\[Theta]", "[", 
       RowBox[{"x", ",", "y", ",", "z"}], "]"}], ",", 
      RowBox[{"{", 
       RowBox[{"x", ",", "1"}], "}"}]}], "]"}], "]"}]}], 
  RowBox[{"(*", 
   SubscriptBox["\[Theta]", "x"], "*)"}]}], "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"d", "=", 
   RowBox[{"FullSimplify", "[", 
    RowBox[{"D", "[", 
     RowBox[{
      RowBox[{"\[Theta]", "[", 
       RowBox[{"x", ",", "y", ",", "z"}], "]"}], ",", 
      RowBox[{"{", 
       RowBox[{"x", ",", "2"}], "}"}]}], "]"}], "]"}]}], 
  RowBox[{"(*", 
   SubscriptBox["\[Theta]", "xx"], "*)"}]}], "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"e", "=", 
   RowBox[{"FullSimplify", "[", 
    RowBox[{"D", "[", 
     RowBox[{
      RowBox[{"\[Phi]", "[", 
       RowBox[{"x", ",", "y", ",", "z"}], "]"}], ",", 
      RowBox[{"{", 
       RowBox[{"x", ",", "1"}], "}"}]}], "]"}], "]"}]}], 
  RowBox[{"(*", 
   SubscriptBox["\[Phi]", "x"], "*)"}]}], "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
 RowBox[{"f", "=", 
  RowBox[{"FullSimplify", "[", 
   RowBox[{"D", "[", 
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{"\[Phi]", "[", 
      RowBox[{"x", ",", "y", ",", "z"}], "]"}], ",", 
     RowBox[{"{", 
      RowBox[{"x", ",", "2"}], "}"}]}], "]"}], "]"}], 
  RowBox[{"(*", 
   SubscriptBox["\[Phi]", "xx"], "*)"}]}]}], "Input",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.861036714455714*^9, 3.8610367678299627`*^9}},
 CellLabel->"In[4]:=",ExpressionUUID->"a28508ee-6380-45c8-9a5f-35394a8f6dd0"],

Cell[BoxData[
 FractionBox["x", 
  SqrtBox[
   RowBox[{
    SuperscriptBox["x", "2"], "+", 
    SuperscriptBox["y", "2"], "+", 
    SuperscriptBox["z", "2"]}]]]], "Output",
 CellChangeTimes->{3.8610367066794863`*^9, 3.861122264189538*^9},
 CellLabel->"Out[4]=",ExpressionUUID->"a6018e93-cdaa-418c-9e60-674f5d4a4e4d"],

Cell[BoxData[
 FractionBox[
  RowBox[{
   SuperscriptBox["y", "2"], "+", 
   SuperscriptBox["z", "2"]}], 
  SuperscriptBox[
   RowBox[{"(", 
    RowBox[{
     SuperscriptBox["x", "2"], "+", 
     SuperscriptBox["y", "2"], "+", 
     SuperscriptBox["z", "2"]}], ")"}], 
   RowBox[{"3", "/", "2"}]]]], "Output",
 CellChangeTimes->{3.8610367066794863`*^9, 3.8611222642130404`*^9},
 CellLabel->"Out[5]=",ExpressionUUID->"7a8297e3-e905-439d-b99d-6de8990c4fba"],

Cell[BoxData[
 FractionBox[
  RowBox[{"x", " ", "z"}], 
  RowBox[{
   SqrtBox[
    RowBox[{
     SuperscriptBox["x", "2"], "+", 
     SuperscriptBox["y", "2"]}]], " ", 
   RowBox[{"(", 
    RowBox[{
     SuperscriptBox["x", "2"], "+", 
     SuperscriptBox["y", "2"], "+", 
     SuperscriptBox["z", "2"]}], ")"}]}]]], "Output",
 CellChangeTimes->{3.8610367066794863`*^9, 3.8611222642458487`*^9},
 CellLabel->"Out[6]=",ExpressionUUID->"0a2cc1a7-a48e-4e61-8499-fcec2361958d"],

Cell[BoxData[
 FractionBox[
  RowBox[{"z", " ", 
   RowBox[{"(", 
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{
      RowBox[{"-", "2"}], " ", 
      SuperscriptBox["x", "4"]}], "-", 
     RowBox[{
      SuperscriptBox["x", "2"], " ", 
      SuperscriptBox["y", "2"]}], "+", 
     SuperscriptBox["y", "4"], "+", 
     RowBox[{
      SuperscriptBox["y", "2"], " ", 
      SuperscriptBox["z", "2"]}]}], ")"}]}], 
  RowBox[{
   SuperscriptBox[
    RowBox[{"(", 
     RowBox[{
      SuperscriptBox["x", "2"], "+", 
      SuperscriptBox["y", "2"]}], ")"}], 
    RowBox[{"3", "/", "2"}]], " ", 
   SuperscriptBox[
    RowBox[{"(", 
     RowBox[{
      SuperscriptBox["x", "2"], "+", 
      SuperscriptBox["y", "2"], "+", 
      SuperscriptBox["z", "2"]}], ")"}], "2"]}]]], "Output",
 CellChangeTimes->{3.8610367066794863`*^9, 3.8611222643215017`*^9},
 CellLabel->"Out[7]=",ExpressionUUID->"3b6bc9b1-a7fb-46ec-b859-952e7e7e5084"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{"-", 
  FractionBox["y", 
   RowBox[{
    SuperscriptBox["x", "2"], "+", 
    SuperscriptBox["y", "2"]}]]}]], "Output",
 CellChangeTimes->{3.8610367066794863`*^9, 3.861122264326973*^9},
 CellLabel->"Out[8]=",ExpressionUUID->"8b966770-af77-48b0-8205-8981bc70abee"],

Cell[BoxData[
 FractionBox[
  RowBox[{"2", " ", "x", " ", "y"}], 
  SuperscriptBox[
   RowBox[{"(", 
    RowBox[{
     SuperscriptBox["x", "2"], "+", 
     SuperscriptBox["y", "2"]}], ")"}], "2"]]], "Output",
 CellChangeTimes->{3.8610367066794863`*^9, 3.8611222643396873`*^9},
 CellLabel->"Out[9]=",ExpressionUUID->"9b1024b1-7739-42d7-9275-0be4e364af58"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Now we can combine all of the above results and get the derivation for ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["u", "xx"], TraditionalForm]],
  FormatType->"TraditionalForm",ExpressionUUID->
  "75600044-9ce8-4f00-8cf8-b682482b1a99"],
 " in terms of (r, \[Theta], \[Phi]):"
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.86103680943064*^9, 
  3.861036865540184*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"69f3ca84-d0d6-4d02-b7cf-\
75b40acae197"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{
  SubscriptBox["u", "xx"], "=", 
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{
    SubscriptBox["u", "\[Rho]\[Rho]"], 
    SuperscriptBox[
     RowBox[{"(", "a", ")"}], "2"]}], "+", 
   RowBox[{
    SubscriptBox["u", "\[Rho]\[Theta]"], 
    RowBox[{"(", 
     RowBox[{"a", "*", "c"}], ")"}]}], "+", 
   RowBox[{
    SubscriptBox["u", "\[Rho]\[Phi]"], 
    RowBox[{"(", 
     RowBox[{"a", "*", "e"}], ")"}]}], "+", 
   RowBox[{
    SubscriptBox["u", "\[Rho]"], 
    RowBox[{"(", "b", ")"}]}], "+", 
   RowBox[{
    SubscriptBox["u", "\[Theta]\[Theta]"], 
    SuperscriptBox[
     RowBox[{"(", "c", ")"}], "2"]}], "+", 
   RowBox[{
    SubscriptBox["u", "\[Theta]\[Rho]"], 
    RowBox[{"(", 
     RowBox[{"c", "*", "a"}], ")"}]}], "+", 
   RowBox[{
    SubscriptBox["u", "\[Theta]\[Phi]"], 
    RowBox[{"(", 
     RowBox[{"c", "*", "e"}], ")"}]}], "+", 
   RowBox[{
    SubscriptBox["u", "\[Theta]"], 
    RowBox[{"(", "b", ")"}]}], "+", 
   RowBox[{
    SubscriptBox["u", "\[Phi]\[Phi]"], 
    SuperscriptBox[
     RowBox[{"(", "e", ")"}], "2"]}], "+", 
   RowBox[{
    SubscriptBox["u", "\[Phi]\[Rho]"], 
    RowBox[{"(", 
     RowBox[{"e", "*", "a"}], ")"}]}], "+", 
   RowBox[{
    SubscriptBox["u", "\[Phi]\[Theta]"], 
    RowBox[{"(", 
     RowBox[{"e", "*", "c"}], ")"}]}], "+", 
   RowBox[{
    SubscriptBox["u", "\[Phi]"], 
    RowBox[{"(", "f", ")"}]}]}]}]], "Input",
 CellLabel->"In[10]:=",ExpressionUUID->"25afa43a-c9b0-4461-9d3b-139a758cfd2d"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{
  FractionBox[
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"(", 
     RowBox[{
      SuperscriptBox["y", "2"], "+", 
      SuperscriptBox["z", "2"]}], ")"}], " ", 
    SubscriptBox["u", "\[Theta]"]}], 
   SuperscriptBox[
    RowBox[{"(", 
     RowBox[{
      SuperscriptBox["x", "2"], "+", 
      SuperscriptBox["y", "2"], "+", 
      SuperscriptBox["z", "2"]}], ")"}], 
    RowBox[{"3", "/", "2"}]]], "+", 
  FractionBox[
   RowBox[{
    SuperscriptBox["x", "2"], " ", 
    SuperscriptBox["z", "2"], " ", 
    SubscriptBox["u", "\[Theta]\[Theta]"]}], 
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"(", 
     RowBox[{
      SuperscriptBox["x", "2"], "+", 
      SuperscriptBox["y", "2"]}], ")"}], " ", 
    SuperscriptBox[
     RowBox[{"(", 
      RowBox[{
       SuperscriptBox["x", "2"], "+", 
       SuperscriptBox["y", "2"], "+", 
       SuperscriptBox["z", "2"]}], ")"}], "2"]}]], "+", 
  FractionBox[
   RowBox[{
    SuperscriptBox["x", "2"], " ", "z", " ", 
    SubscriptBox["u", "\[Theta]\[Rho]"]}], 
   RowBox[{
    SqrtBox[
     RowBox[{
      SuperscriptBox["x", "2"], "+", 
      SuperscriptBox["y", "2"]}]], " ", 
    SuperscriptBox[
     RowBox[{"(", 
      RowBox[{
       SuperscriptBox["x", "2"], "+", 
       SuperscriptBox["y", "2"], "+", 
       SuperscriptBox["z", "2"]}], ")"}], 
     RowBox[{"3", "/", "2"}]]}]], "-", 
  FractionBox[
   RowBox[{"x", " ", "y", " ", "z", " ", 
    SubscriptBox["u", "\[Theta]\[Phi]"]}], 
   RowBox[{
    SuperscriptBox[
     RowBox[{"(", 
      RowBox[{
       SuperscriptBox["x", "2"], "+", 
       SuperscriptBox["y", "2"]}], ")"}], 
     RowBox[{"3", "/", "2"}]], " ", 
    RowBox[{"(", 
     RowBox[{
      SuperscriptBox["x", "2"], "+", 
      SuperscriptBox["y", "2"], "+", 
      SuperscriptBox["z", "2"]}], ")"}]}]], "+", 
  FractionBox[
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"(", 
     RowBox[{
      SuperscriptBox["y", "2"], "+", 
      SuperscriptBox["z", "2"]}], ")"}], " ", 
    SubscriptBox["u", "\[Rho]"]}], 
   SuperscriptBox[
    RowBox[{"(", 
     RowBox[{
      SuperscriptBox["x", "2"], "+", 
      SuperscriptBox["y", "2"], "+", 
      SuperscriptBox["z", "2"]}], ")"}], 
    RowBox[{"3", "/", "2"}]]], "+", 
  FractionBox[
   RowBox[{
    SuperscriptBox["x", "2"], " ", "z", " ", 
    SubscriptBox["u", "\[Rho]\[Theta]"]}], 
   RowBox[{
    SqrtBox[
     RowBox[{
      SuperscriptBox["x", "2"], "+", 
      SuperscriptBox["y", "2"]}]], " ", 
    SuperscriptBox[
     RowBox[{"(", 
      RowBox[{
       SuperscriptBox["x", "2"], "+", 
       SuperscriptBox["y", "2"], "+", 
       SuperscriptBox["z", "2"]}], ")"}], 
     RowBox[{"3", "/", "2"}]]}]], "+", 
  FractionBox[
   RowBox[{
    SuperscriptBox["x", "2"], " ", 
    SubscriptBox["u", "\[Rho]\[Rho]"]}], 
   RowBox[{
    SuperscriptBox["x", "2"], "+", 
    SuperscriptBox["y", "2"], "+", 
    SuperscriptBox["z", "2"]}]], "-", 
  FractionBox[
   RowBox[{"x", " ", "y", " ", 
    SubscriptBox["u", "\[Rho]\[Phi]"]}], 
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"(", 
     RowBox[{
      SuperscriptBox["x", "2"], "+", 
      SuperscriptBox["y", "2"]}], ")"}], " ", 
    SqrtBox[
     RowBox[{
      SuperscriptBox["x", "2"], "+", 
      SuperscriptBox["y", "2"], "+", 
      SuperscriptBox["z", "2"]}]]}]], "+", 
  FractionBox[
   RowBox[{"2", " ", "x", " ", "y", " ", 
    SubscriptBox["u", "\[Phi]"]}], 
   SuperscriptBox[
    RowBox[{"(", 
     RowBox[{
      SuperscriptBox["x", "2"], "+", 
      SuperscriptBox["y", "2"]}], ")"}], "2"]], "-", 
  FractionBox[
   RowBox[{"x", " ", "y", " ", "z", " ", 
    SubscriptBox["u", "\[Phi]\[Theta]"]}], 
   RowBox[{
    SuperscriptBox[
     RowBox[{"(", 
      RowBox[{
       SuperscriptBox["x", "2"], "+", 
       SuperscriptBox["y", "2"]}], ")"}], 
     RowBox[{"3", "/", "2"}]], " ", 
    RowBox[{"(", 
     RowBox[{
      SuperscriptBox["x", "2"], "+", 
      SuperscriptBox["y", "2"], "+", 
      SuperscriptBox["z", "2"]}], ")"}]}]], "-", 
  FractionBox[
   RowBox[{"x", " ", "y", " ", 
    SubscriptBox["u", "\[Phi]\[Rho]"]}], 
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"(", 
     RowBox[{
      SuperscriptBox["x", "2"], "+", 
      SuperscriptBox["y", "2"]}], ")"}], " ", 
    SqrtBox[
     RowBox[{
      SuperscriptBox["x", "2"], "+", 
      SuperscriptBox["y", "2"], "+", 
      SuperscriptBox["z", "2"]}]]}]], "+", 
  FractionBox[
   RowBox[{
    SuperscriptBox["y", "2"], " ", 
    SubscriptBox["u", "\[Phi]\[Phi]"]}], 
   SuperscriptBox[
    RowBox[{"(", 
     RowBox[{
      SuperscriptBox["x", "2"], "+", 
      SuperscriptBox["y", "2"]}], ")"}], "2"]]}]], "Output",
 CellChangeTimes->{3.8610368726602793`*^9, 3.8611222643481903`*^9},
 CellLabel->"Out[10]=",ExpressionUUID->"0e151df4-ed4a-47c4-b1cc-89347e2adb77"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell["\<\
Obviously this answer is a lot to work with, but putting it in a Mathematica \
document greatly simplifies the grunt work. Imagine having to work this out \
by hand. \
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8610368796033373`*^9, 
  3.8610369513767633`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"d154dd78-2d5b-4b9e-af2d-\
dd031317bbf7"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["\<\
2.) Discuss the forms found in Spherical coordinates\[LongDash]both of the \
ODEs and their solutions. Do some research into Legendre\[CloseCurlyQuote]s \
differential equation, functions, and the resulting spherical harmonics. \
Summarize your takeaways and cite all references.\
\>", "Chapter",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.861037027623884*^9, 
  3.861037110289773*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"f6543925-7c3a-423c-b580-\
cee13d5a9288"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "\tMuch like our previous solutions in polar, our current solutions in \
spherical produce long, complicated solutions with lots of trig functions. It\
\[CloseCurlyQuote]s also worth noting that many more partial derivatives need \
to be taken since we\[CloseCurlyQuote]re dealing with a higher dimension. \
Tediousness aside, we can begin analyzing the results. To my surprise, the \
ODE for the azimuthal angle\[LongDash]\[CapitalPhi]\[CloseCurlyQuote]\
\[CloseCurlyQuote]+\[Lambda]*\[CapitalPhi] =0\[LongDash]is the exact same ODE \
that we\[CloseCurlyQuote]ve solved countless times in this class, and can do \
so once again right here. Even the equation for ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{"R", "\[LongDash]", 
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{
      RowBox[{
       SuperscriptBox["\[Rho]", "2"], 
       RowBox[{"R", "''"}]}], "+", 
      RowBox[{"2", 
       RowBox[{"\[Rho]R", "'"}]}], "-", "\[Mu]R"}], "=", "0"}]}], 
   TraditionalForm]],
  FormatType->"TraditionalForm",ExpressionUUID->
  "aa3f4251-8402-433b-86f3-72fc1b309735"],
 "\[LongDash]isn\[CloseCurlyQuote]t too dissimilar; this particular Euler \
equation can be solved using previous ODE techniques and is even similar to \
what we saw in polar. \[CapitalTheta], however, is another story. Converting \
the \[CapitalTheta] equation requires a change of variables which is tedious \
in itself. For brevity sake, I\[CloseCurlyQuote]m just going to list the \
final answer here: ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{
      SuperscriptBox[
       RowBox[{"(", 
        RowBox[{"Sin", "[", "\[Theta]", "]"}], ")"}], "2"], "*", 
      SubscriptBox["\[CapitalTheta]", "ss"]}], "-", 
     RowBox[{"2", 
      RowBox[{"Cos", "[", "\[Theta]", "]"}], "*", 
      SubscriptBox["\[CapitalTheta]", "s"]}], "+", 
     RowBox[{
      RowBox[{"(", 
       RowBox[{"\[Mu]", "-", 
        FractionBox[
         SuperscriptBox["m", "2"], 
         SuperscriptBox[
          RowBox[{"(", 
           RowBox[{"Sin", "[", "\[CapitalTheta]", "]"}], ")"}], "2"]]}], 
       ")"}], "*", "\[CapitalTheta]"}]}], "=", "0"}], TraditionalForm]],
  FormatType->"TraditionalForm",ExpressionUUID->
  "369bfb3c-411c-47de-89c5-f72ee0059400"],
 ". I personally didn\[CloseCurlyQuote]t recognize this equation at first, \
but was able to figure out what was going on after reading the provided \
notes. To quote the text directly: \n\n\tThis is actually an associated \
Legendre differential equation, as it doesn\[CloseCurlyQuote]t exactly match \
the form above. In the symmetric case, the last term is simplified to match \
the form of Legendre\[CloseCurlyQuote]s differential equation.\n\tFor these \
solutions, we define the solutions in terms of m and \[Mu]=n(n+1) through the \
associated Legendre functions denoted ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    SubscriptBox[
     RowBox[{"(", 
      SuperscriptBox["P", "m"], ")"}], "n"], 
    RowBox[{"Cos", "[", "\[Theta]", "]"}]}], TraditionalForm]],
  FormatType->"TraditionalForm",ExpressionUUID->
  "3b801e37-9e7c-4965-8c59-5e2a68a87040"],
 ".\n\t\t\t\t  -(",
 StyleBox["Partial Differential Equations-An Exploration in Modeling Our \
Physical World",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 ", Dr. Shelley Poole, 118)\nThis begs the question: what is a Legendre \
Polynomial? Time for some outside sources. \n\n\tWhen researching Legendre\
\[CloseCurlyQuote]s differential equation, my first stop was to the assigned \
textbook for our class. As it turns out, the textbook is extremely detailed \
on Legendre Polynomials and related topics. For brevity sakes, I\
\[CloseCurlyQuote]m going to reference the text exclusively from here on out. \
That said, let\[CloseCurlyQuote]s talk about what it has to offer. \n\t\n\t\
The text goes into great detail about solving the equation using power \
series, and also mentions how the series will converge for |x| < 1. We can \
use techniques that we learned back in ODEs to accomplish this task, so there\
\[CloseCurlyQuote]s no new math here. However, it\[CloseCurlyQuote]s \
important to point out that several relations arise from this approach, such \
as Bonnet\[CloseCurlyQuote]s (again, this is discussed in the book). In \
regards to spherical harmonics, these functions arise when working on the \
surface of a sphere, and so these phenomena are going to pop up here. The \
text gives a formal definition on page 284, so I\[CloseCurlyQuote]m just \
going to refer you to that page for details as well as the following pages \
for how spherical harmonics can be used to solve particular PDEs. In all, \
these are interesting fields of study that may pop up again in higher level \
math classes. "
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.861062711918356*^9, 3.8610628867215633`*^9}, {
  3.861062968112446*^9, 3.861063053490724*^9}, {3.861063085227099*^9, 
  3.861063214744331*^9}, {3.861063350003793*^9, 3.861063392356908*^9}, {
  3.8610634238677692`*^9, 3.861063545878125*^9}, {3.8610635795630827`*^9, 
  3.861064029085998*^9}, {3.861064116420578*^9, 3.861064143330063*^9}, {
  3.861064553141449*^9, 3.8610645929306173`*^9}, {3.8610647138355103`*^9, 
  3.8610647352163067`*^9}, {3.861067527792348*^9, 3.861067633907364*^9}, {
  3.861067774223178*^9, 3.861067917507139*^9}, {3.861067949199399*^9, 
  3.8610679740760717`*^9}, {3.8610680305505047`*^9, 3.861068042885907*^9}, {
  3.8610680780264683`*^9, 3.861068096154111*^9}, {3.861068245516333*^9, 
  3.8610683103483553`*^9}, {3.861068352641469*^9, 3.861068365683833*^9}, {
  3.86106862101633*^9, 
  3.861068799488063*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"3dc23652-62c8-4799-ba51-\
baf7b034297b"]
}, Open  ]]
}, Open  ]]
},
